ONE person was killed and four others injured on Wednesday, 14 July, after they were run over by two cars on Inanda Road in KZN. Arrive Alive spokeswoman Wendy Watson said the Reaction Unit South Africa was called to the scene by community members who were operating a roadblock to assist with recent mob attacks. “On arrival, one person was located in the bush. He had suffered life-threatening injuries and died at the scene,’ said Watson. ALSO WATCH: WATCH: WOMAN CRASHES AFTER LETTING GOD DRIVE! “A second one was critically injured while three other men sustained moderate injuries.” Watson said they established that a white Honda ran over two men, and the driver stopped to help when the community started to damage his vehicle. “A second unknown car overtook and ran over three men from the mob. The second vehicle did not stop. The injured were transported privately to the hospital.” 